pixelated.declaration:
image-rendering: -webkit-optimize-contrast; /* Safari */
			image-rendering: -o-crisp-edges; /* OS X & Windows Opera (12.02+) */
			image-rendering: pixelated; /* in case crisp-edges isn't supported */
			image-rendering: crisp-edges; /* the recommended pixel art setting according to MDN */

row.comment: can be used to override the direction of a `.box`

pane.comment: A pane is a box floating over the page, like for dialogs. By default it's opaque, resetting the background to the initial depth.

panel.comment: A panel is a box embedded into the page, useful for visually isolating content.

plain.comment: TODO maybe this belongs with the reset, like `selected`? or does `selected` belong here?
